    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In Dutch history, regarded as the century from the conclusion of the Twelve Years’ Truce in 1609 until either the death of Prince William III in 1702 or the conclusion of the Peace of Utrecht in 1713. It was an era of political, economic, and cultural growth during which the Netherlands became one of the most powerful and influential in Europe and the world.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
